### CancelLoadTracking -> LoadTrackingStoppedEvent (Reason: CANCELLED)
###
### Separate VectorID from the TrackLoad tests so its row count is unambiguous.

POST http://localhost:5129/api/truckertoolstracking/CancelLoadTracking
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "VectorID": 999002,
    "loadNumber": "999002",
    "loadTrackExternalId": "999002",
    "carrier": {
        "companyName": "Test Carrier LLC",
        "docketNumber": "MC-999002"
    },
    "driverName": "Test Driver",
    "driverCell": "555-0100",
    "shipper": {
        "shipperId": "0",
        "emails": "",
        "emailInterval": "",
        "referenceNumber": ""
    }
}

###
# Expected:
#   - HTTP 200 with TrackingResponse
#   - 1 row in VendorOutboundTransactions for VectorLoadId='999002':
#       EventTypeName  = 'LoadTrackingStoppedEvent'
#       RequestPayload reason = "CANCELLED"
#
# Verify with query #3 in 99_VerifySQL.sql.
#
# curl equivalent:
#   curl -X POST http://localhost:5129/api/truckertoolstracking/CancelLoadTracking ^
